content: I've seen common yellowthroats at the nearby nature reserve where I go birding with my group. We've had some great sightings there, and it's always exciting to see them flitting around in the wetlands. Speaking of which, I've been keeping a birding journal for the past six months, and it's been really helping me keep track of my sightings. I've seen a total of 43 species since I started, and it's amazing to look back and see how far I've come.
